      "link": "https://www.audible.com/es_US/podcast/James-Harden-Audio-Biography/B0D8JP46Q4",
      "snippet": "James Harden - Audio Biography Escúchala gratis Narrado por: Cerrar De: Cerrar James Edward Harden Jr. was born on August 26, 1989, in Los Angeles, California. Growing up in the Compton neighborhood, Harden developed a passion for basketball at an early age. He attended Artesia High School in Lakewood, California, where he led his team to two state championships. His impressive performance earned him recognition as a McDonald's All-American in 2007. College Career Harden continued his basketball journey at Arizona State University, where he played for the Sun Devils. During his two seasons with the team (2007-2009), Harden showcased his scoring ability and all-around game. He was named the Pac-10 Player of the Year in 2009 and earned consensus All-American honors. Harden declared for the NBA draft after his sophomore year, solidifying his reputation as one of the top prospects in the nation. NBA Career Oklahoma City Thunder (2009-2012) Harden was selected as the third overall pick by t",
